description: TEHRAN- Hezbollah Secretary General Seyyed Hassan Nasrallah has played down Israel’s threats of waging a full-scale war against the Lebanese resistance group.
title: Nasrallah: Over one hundred thousand Hezbollah fighters ready to join war

description: TEHRAN-Neauphle-le-Chateau Theater in Tehran is hosting the play “Rosencrantz and Guildenstern Are Dead” written by Tom Stoppard.
title: Tom Stoppard’s “Rosencrantz and Guildenstern Are Dead” on stage in Tehran

description: TEHRAN- Shahrzad Theater Complex in Tehran will be playing host to a reading performance of the renowned American playwright Neil Simon’s comic fable “Fools” on Friday.
title: Tehran theater to host reading performance of Neil Simon’s “Fools”

description: TEHRAN- The first edition of the "Service to Martyrdom" poetry festival, a commemoration of the 40th day after the martyrdom of President Ebrahim Raisi and his companions, is set to take place in Robat Karim, Tehran province, in July with international participation; the organizers have announced.
title: “Service to Martyrdom” poetry festival to be held with international participation

description: TEHRAN-Iran is present at the 30th Beijing International Book Fair (BIBF) that commenced in Beijing, China, on Wednesday.
title: Iran participating in 30th Beijing International Book Fair

description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper addressed the successful path of the 13th government in foreign policy and wrote: After the 13th government headed by Ayatollah Raisi came to power, the country's diplomatic apparatus changed course from western-centrism to multilateralism, developing cooperation with neighboring countries and resuming relations with neighboring countries.
title: Diplomacy of honor and resistance

description: TEHRAN – With less than ten days remaining before the June 28th presidential election, candidates have hit the road in a last-minute push for votes.
title: Candidates hit the road for votes

description: TEHRAN - More than eight months into Israel’s brutal onslaught on the Gaza Strip, about 37,400 Palestinians have lost their lives and nearly 86,000 others have been injured.
title: Israel will fail to crush the Palestinians’ iron will

description: TEHRAN- Israeli media has described the drone surveillance footage released by Lebanon's Hezbollah as "extremely dangerous," saying that Israeli censorship prevented its circulation in Hebrew media and classified it as “disturbing".
title: ‘Hoopoe’ drone video “extremely dangerous”

description: MADRID Last week, the Lebanese newspaper Al-Akhbar, citing reliable sources, reported that Beirut had received diplomatic messages indicating an imminent attack by Israel.
title: Hezbollah seeking to compel Israel to change its behavior and calculations

description: The October 7 attack on Israel and the subsequent military operation in Gaza did not occur in a vacuum as they were preceded by decades of violence and retribution against Palestinians, UN Commissioner Navi Pillay said Wednesday.
title: UN official: Oct. 7 attack on Israel did not occur in vacuum

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and North Korean leader Kim Jong Un signed an agreement Wednesday that pledges mutual aid if either country faces “aggression,” a strategic pact that comes as both face escalating standoffs with the West.
title: Russia and North Korea sign partnership deal

description: US Senator Bernie Sanders said his country should withhold sending Israel “all offensive military aid” after the Israeli prime minister attacked the pace at which the US was supplying him bombs to use in Gaza.
title: Sander: Stop military aid to Israel

description: Europe has a duty to host children hurt and traumatized by war in Gaza for as long as the conflict continues, Greek Foreign Minister George Gerapetritis told Reuters on Wednesday.
title: Greece: Europe must host Gaza children

description: TEHRAN – The acting Foreign Minister of Iran says the country’s foreign policy apparatus continues to actively pursue the demands of the country, its people, and the community.
title: Iran’s foreign policy to continue pursuing demands of nation: Baqeri

description: TEHRAN– Commander of the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC) Major General Hossein Salami says Iran has solidified the utmost level of national strength and resilience by reaching the peak of its military and political power.
title: IRGC commander praises national strength, resilience amidst challenges

description: TEHRAN – Ali Baqeri Kani, the acting Foreign Minister of Iran, has met with Qatar's Prime Minister Sheikh Mohammed bin Abdulrahman bin Jassim al-Thani in his brief visit to Doha, Qatar on Wednesday.
title: Iran acting FM meets Qatari PM in Doha

description: TEHRAN - Iran's ambassador to the United Nations, Saeed Iravani, has condemned U.S. sanctions as a hindrance to Tehran's efforts to combat the illicit trade of small arms and light weapons in the region.
title: Sanctions hindering fight against illicit arms trade: Iran UN envoy

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Navy Commander Rear Admiral Shahram Irani announced on Wednesday that the country’s naval forces have developed high combat and defense forces with the help of sophisticated homegrown drones.
title: Iran Navy equipped with cutting-edge drones: commander

description: TEHRAN – The mayor of Tehran who is currently running for president said he is not opposed to negotiating with the West to reduce tensions, but won’t tolerate disrespect and deceit solely for the sake of engaging in talks with Western states.
title: Zakani says not averse to talks with West

description: TEHRAN - This fall, Iran and Iraq will jointly host a pilgrimage car rally, a 4,000-kilometer journey from Karbala to Mashhad and back.
title: Iran, Iraq to host pilgrimage car rally

description: TEHRAN – The ancient city of Khorramabad has introduced a virtual tour, featuring 360-degree photography and aerial views, to spotlight its key historical and natural attractions.
title: Khorramabad launches virtual tourism with 360-degree views

description: TEHRAN – On Tuesday, a magnitude 5 earthquake caused damage to several historical buildings in Kashmar, a historical city in eastern Iran.
title: Earthquake damages historical buildings in Kashmar

description: TEHRAN - The ancient city of Boroujerd, located in the western Lorestan province, is home to a rich collection of architectural gems.
title: From Sassanid temples to Seljuk mosques: discover rich heritage of Boroujerd

description: TEHRAN – On Wednesday, the Ministry of Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts held a ceremony to unveil innovative tourism content aimed at attracting more foreign visitors.
title: Tourism ministry reveals special content aimed to boost arrivals

description: Delegations from dozens of countries have arrived in the Russian city of Khanty-Mansiysk for the XV International IT Forum with the participation of BRICS and SCO countries. The event is being organised under Russia's chairmanship of BRICS in 2024. TV BRICS is the international media partner of the event.
title: BRICS, SCO, Africa and Latin America to discuss digital development at IT forum

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian football season is set to reach its climax with the exciting Hazfi Cup final between Sepahan and Mes, taking place on Thursday at the Azadi Stadium in Tehran. This high-stakes match will feature the use of VAR technology, ensuring fair and precise decision-making.
title: Thrilling Hazfi Cup final to conclude Iran's football season

description: Following the results of the fifth day of the BRICS Games, Russia topped the medal standings with 239 medals. Of these, 112 were gold, 78 silver and 49 bronze.
title: Russia, China and Belarus lead medal standings of BRICS Games

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated the U.S. 3-2 (26-28, 25-23, 25-18, 26-28, 15-13) in the 2024 Volleyball Nations League (VNL) Week 3 on Wednesday.
title: Iran edge the U.S. at 2024 VNL

description: TEHRAN –During the past academic year (September 2023 – June 2024),  the Ministry of Education managed to enroll about 20 percent of out-of-school nomad students, an official with the Ministry of Education has said.
title: 20% of out-of-school nomad students start education

description: TEHRAN – The eighth day of Aban – the 8th Iranian calendar month, which falls on October 29, has been approved to be registered on the national calendar as the ‘Ranger Day’, Nourollah Moradi, an official with the Department of Environment, has said.
title: ‘Ranger Day’ on national calendar

description: TEHRAN –Each year, World Refugee Day is celebrated on June 20 to honor people who have been forced to flee due to conflict, violence, or persecution.
title: Iran’s generous support for refugees

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s new PMI data for the fiscal month of Ordibehesht (April 20 – May 20, 2024), released by the Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA) has raised concern about the industry sector.
title: Iran’s monthly PMI raises concern about industry sector

description: TEHRAN - The Central Bank of Iran (CBI) says it is planning to introduce a digital currency (CBDC) to facilitate purchases for the clients of the banking network in the country.
title: CBI looking into piloting digital currency

description: TEHRAN - Iran exported $400 million of home appliances in the previous Iranian calendar year (March 21, 20203 to March 19, 2024), showing an 18.2 percent hike compared to a year earlier.
title: Iran exports $400m of home appliances in a year

description: TEHRAN - Tehran and Seoul discussed their experiences in urban regeneration with the centrality of community-based planning at Iran’s Urban Regeneration Corporation on June 10.
title: Tehran, Seoul share experiences in urban regeneration

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s minister of Industry, Mining, and Trade said 1.5 million cars will be produced in the country by the end of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20, 2025).
title: Iran to produce 1.5 million cars by March 2025

description: BEIJING- The Closing Ceremony of the Program on China Development Studies and Media Exchange for the China International Press Communication Center (CIPCC)2024 was held at Renmin University of China (RUC) on Tuesday.
title: CIPCC 2024 program closing ceremony held at Renmin University of China

description: TEHRAN - The Rasht-Caspian Railway Project in Iran’s northern province of Gilan will be inaugurated on June 20, 2024.
title: Rasht-Caspian railway to be inaugurated this week

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji has said that over the first three years of the 13th administration in office, 150 oil industry projects, worth $34 billion, have become active.
title: 150 projects worth $34b launched in past 3 years: Oji

description: TEHRAN – Mohammadamin Tabatabaei of Iran won a bronze medal at the 5th Stepan Avagyan Memorial 2024.
title: Iran’s Tabatabaei wins bronze at Avagyan memorial

description: TEHRAN – Abbasali Nategh Nouri was elected as president of Iran Federation of Sport Associations on Wednesday.
title: Nategh Nouri elected president of Iran Federation of Sport Associations
